{"image_id": "KMB_2010_page_23", "image_size": [1275, 1650], "ocr": [{"text": "PART II", "bbox": [162.5, 158.9, 240.5, 179.7]}, {"text": "(Continued)", "bbox": [162.5, 184.1, 263.2, 204.9]}, {"text": "resulted from price increases implemented in most markets in 2008, net of 2009 increased promotional", "bbox": [237.5, 242.4, 1112.3, 263.2]}, {"text": "activity. Unfavorable currency effects were primarily attributable to South Korea, Russia, Australia and", "bbox": [237.5, 267.4, 1112.5, 288.2]}, {"text": "Latin America.", "bbox": [237.5, 292.4, 363.7, 313.2]}, {"text": "•", "bbox": [204.2, 330.1, 211.5, 350.9]}, {"text": "Economic weakness and high unemployment levels in North America and Europe continued to affect", "bbox": [237.5, 330.1, 1112.3, 350.9]}, {"text": "K-C Professional’s categories in 2009. In North America, sales decreased 4 percent, due to a decrease in", "bbox": [237.5, 355.1, 1112.5, 375.9]}, {"text": "sales volumes of 6 percent (which is net of an approximate 4 percent benefit from the acquisition of", "bbox": [237.5, 380.1, 1112.5, 400.9]}, {"text": "Jackson in April 2009), partially offset by higher net selling prices of about 3 percent. In Europe, sales", "bbox": [237.5, 405.1, 1112.4, 425.9]}, {"text": "of K-C Professional products decreased 16 percent, due to a decrease in sales volumes of 9 percent", "bbox": [237.5, 430.1, 1112.4, 450.9]}, {"text": "(which is net of an approximate 1 percent benefit from the Jackson acquisition) and unfavorable", "bbox": [237.5, 455.1, 1112.3, 475.9]}, {"text": "currency effects of 9 percent, partially offset by higher net selling prices of 3 percent.", "bbox": [237.5, 480.1, 950.6, 500.9]}, {"text": "•", "bbox": [204.2, 517.8, 211.5, 538.7]}, {"text": "The increased sales volumes for health care products were primarily due to broad-based growth across", "bbox": [237.5, 517.8, 1112.4, 538.7]}, {"text": "several categories including exam gloves and apparel and a 2 percent benefit from the acquisition of", "bbo